{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016e4tyTkUBW8tRNbNu3WncM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented for US-020:\n\n## US-020 - Temperature system with heat diffusion\n\n### Changes\n\n**Step1 kernel** (`step1.cu`):\n- Added `temperature_in` input and `dTdt_out` output\n- Heat diffusion computed in the neighbor loop: `dTdt += kappa_i * viscosity_lap_coeff * sum_j (m_j/rho_j) * (T_j - T_i) * (h - |r|)`\n- `kappa_i` read from `c_materials[mat_id].thermal_conductivity`\n- Self-interaction skipped for heat diffusion\n\n**Integrate kernel** (`integrate.cu`):\n- Added `sorted_dTdt` input, `temperature_out` output\n- Temperature integration: `T += dTdt * dt - 0.1 * (T - 293.0) * dt`, clamped to [0, 5000]\n- Applied in all code paths (static, sleeping, normal)\n\n**Python wrappers**: `step1.py` (3-tuple return, materials upload), `integrate.py` (6-tuple return), `simulation.py` (wired dTdt through pipeline), `world.py` (sorted_dTdt buffer)\n\n### Test results\n- **All 18 step1 tests pass** (3 new heat diffusion tests)\n- **All 29 integrate tests pass** (updated unpacking)\n- **All 14 step2 tests pass** (no regressions)\n- Hot particle (1000K) among cold (293K): dTdt negative for hot, positive for cold neighbors\n- Uniform temperature: dTdt = 0\n- Metal conducts 83x faster than water (matches theoretical 50/0.6 = 83.3x)\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":483,"cache_read_input_tokens":130256,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":483},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e6e8b27e-e279-4052-ba7d-ce90d33ff805","uuid":"3bf9edc8-f1be-4929-838f-8861e9d83339"}
